module.exports = [{"country":"Malaysia","description":"Malaysia is a Southeast Asian country occupying parts of the Malay Peninsula and the island of Borneo. It's known for its beaches, rainforests and mix of Malay, Chinese, Indian and European cultural influences. The capital, Kuala Lumpur, is home to colonial buildings, busy shopping districts such as Bukit Bintang and skyscrapers such as the iconic, 451m-tall Petronas Twin Towers.","currency":"Malaysian ringgit","attractions":[{"place":"Petronas Towers","describe":"Iconic skyscrapers towering 88 floors","imageUrl":"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNeIslWlo_CCwFBgineFP-I1jJXkFZ6SWsCXxts=w240-h160-k-no"},{"place":"Genting Highlands","describe":"Hill resort & Genting Skyway cable car","imageUrl":"http://www.alectravelguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/GentingHighlandsResort.jpg"},{"place":"Batu Caves","describe":"Hindu temple set in limestone caves","imageUrl":"http://static.asiawebdirect.com/m/kl/portals/kuala-lumpur-ws/homepage/attractions/batu-caves/pagePropertiesImage/batu-caves.jpg"},{"place":"Legoland Malaysia Resort","describe":"Vibrant hotel with 2 eateries & a pool","imageUrl":"https://goticket.my/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/LEGOLANDArc2-resize-1214x809.jpg"}]},{"country":"Singapore","description":"Singapore, an island city-state off southern Malaysia, is a global financial center with a tropical climate and multicultural population. Its colonial core centers on the Padang, a cricket field since the 1830s and now flanked by grand buildings such as City Hall, with its 18 Corinthian columns. In Singapore's circa-1820 Chinatown stands the red-and-gold Buddha Tooth Relic Temple, said to house one of Buddha's teeth.","currency":"Singapore dollar","attractions":[{"place":"Gardens by the Bay","describe":"Modern public gardens on reclaimed land","imageUrl":"https://www.lokopoko.travel/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/gardens-by-the-bay_wonderwardrobes.jpg"},{"place":"Universal Studios Singapore","describe":"Movie- & TV-themed amusement park","imageUrl":"http://buffalotrip.com/image/cache/data/2016/Singapore/Universal-studios/universal-studio-singapore-tourist-attractions-opening-hours-address-map-guide-tickets-geting-there-travel-tips-37-760x432.JPG"},{"place":"Merlion Park","describe":"Half-lion, half-fish statue & fountain","imageUrl":"https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/0c/33/db/19/merlion-park-with-the.jpg"},{"place":"Night Safari, Singapore","describe":"Zoo for nocturnal animals opened in 1994","imageUrl":"https://cdn.mylittleadventure.com/6756/600x400/singapore-zoo-night-safari-with-tram-ride-vDtOqmFf.jpg"}]},{"country":"Thailand","description":"Thailand is a Southeast Asian country. It's known for tropical beaches, opulent royal palaces, ancient ruins and ornate temples displaying figures of Buddha. In Bangkok, the capital, an ultramodern cityscape rises next to quiet canalside communities and the iconic temples of Wat Arun, Wat Pho and the Emerald Buddha Temple (Wat Phra Kaew). Nearby beach resorts include bustling Pattaya and fashionable Hua Hin.","currency":"Thai baht","attractions":[{"place":"Grand Palace","describe":"Opulent former royal residence & museum","imageUrl":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/25/Grand_Palace_Bangkok%2C_Thailand.jpg/1200px-Grand_Palace_Bangkok%2C_Thailand.jpg"},{"place":"Phi Phi Islands","describe":"Beach, snorkeling, seaside resort, scuba diving, and nightlife","imageUrl":"https://previews.123rf.com/images/iakov/iakov1303/iakov130300040/18371068-maya-bay-phi-phi-leh-island-thailand.jpg"},{"place":"Wat Arun","describe":"Riverside temple with a landmark spire","imageUrl":"http://static.asiawebdirect.com/m/bangkok/portals/bangkok-com/homepage/attraction-temple/wat-arun/pagePropertiesImage/wat-arun-in-bangkok.jpg"},{"place":"Wat Phra That Doi Suthep","describe":"Gilded wat with a storied white elephant","imageUrl":"https://static.thousandwonders.net/Wat.Phra.That.Doi.Suthep.original.6552.jpg"}]},{"country":"Myanmar","description":"Myanmar (formerly Burma) is a Southeast Asian nation of more than 100 ethnic groups, bordering India, Bangladesh, China, Laos and Thailand. Yangon (formerly Rangoon), the country's largest city, is home to bustling markets, numerous parks and lakes, and the towering, gilded Shwedagon Pagoda, which contains Buddhist relics and dates to the 6th century.","currency":"Burmese kyat","attractions":[{"place":"Shwedagon Pagoda","describe":"Large gilded stupa with a visitor center","imageUrl":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/Shwedagon_Pagoda_2017.jpg/1200px-Shwedagon_Pagoda_2017.jpg"},{"place":"Inle Lake","describe":"Lake, monastery, fishing, temple, and buddhism","imageUrl":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d8/Inle_Lake_%28Myanmar%29.jpg"},{"place":"Ananda Temple","describe":"Grand 12th-century Buddhist temple","imageUrl":"https://previews.123rf.com/images/axel2001/axel20011109/axel2001110900022/10458492-white-ananda-temple-in-bagan-myanmar-burma-.jpg"},{"place":"Chauk-htat-gyi Buddha Temple","describe":"Iconic spot with a huge reclining Buddha","imageUrl":"http://c8.alamy.com/comp/AX6MFY/buddha-statue-at-buddhist-temple-chauk-htat-gyi-pagoda-yangon-myanmar-AX6MFY.jpg"}]},{"country":"Indonesia","description":"Indonesia, a Southeast Asian nation made up of thousands of volcanic islands, is home to hundreds of ethnic groups speaking many different languages. It’s known for beaches, volcanoes, Komodo dragons and jungles sheltering elephants, orangutans and tigers. On the island of Java lies Indonesia's vibrant, sprawling capital, Jakarta, and the city of Yogyakarta, known for gamelan music and traditional puppetry.","currency":"Indonesian rupiah","attractions":[{"place":"Tanah Lot","describe":"Island temple with water views","imageUrl":"http://static.asiawebdirect.com/m/bangkok/portals/bali-indonesia-com/homepage/magazine/tanah-lot/pagePropertiesImage/tanah-lot-bali.jpg.jpg"},{"place":"Borobudur","describe":"Iconic & historic Buddhist temple","imageUrl":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/tDuhIrzBjbQ/maxresdefault.jpg"},{"place":"Prambanan","describe":"Ornate, ancient Hindu temple","imageUrl":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/MhifUwbQj6o/maxresdefault.jpg"},{"place":"Ubud Monkey Forest","describe":"Temple complex with many monkeys","imageUrl":"http://seektheworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/1G6A0218.jpg"}]},{"country":"Cambodia","description":"Cambodia is a Southeast Asian nation whose landscape spans low-lying plains, the Mekong Delta, mountains and Gulf of Thailand coastline. Phnom Penh, its capital, is home to the art deco Central Market, glittering Royal Palace and the National Museum's historical and archaeological exhibits. In the country's northwest are the ruins of Angkor Wat, a massive stone temple complex built during the Khmer Empire.","currency":"Cambodian riel","attractions":[{"place":"Angkor Wat","describe":"Massive temple with an ornate design","imageUrl":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Angkor_Wat.jpg/1200px-Angkor_Wat.jpg"},{"place":"Royal Palace, Phnom Penh","describe":"Landmark palace complex built in 1866","imageUrl":"http://static.asiawebdirect.com/m/bangkok/portals/cambodia/homepage/phnom-penh/royal-palace/pagePropertiesImage/phnom-penh-royal-palace.jpg.jpg"},{"place":"Tonlé Sap","describe":"Lake, river, fishing, archaeological site, and temple","imageUrl":"http://static.asiawebdirect.com/m/bangkok/portals/cambodia/homepage/siem-reap/tonle-sap-lake/pagePropertiesImage/tonle-sap-lake.jpg.jpg"},{"place":"Banteay Srei","describe":"Temple, archaeological site, and sculpture","imageUrl":"https://lonelyplanetimages.imgix.net/a/g/hi/t/3e65526c71d23a193d0b24a75f9e27ac-banteay-srei.jpg?auto=enhance&w=770&h=430&fit=crop"}]},{"country":"Vietnam","description":"Vietnam is a Southeast Asian country on the South China Sea known for its beaches, rivers, Buddhist pagodas and bustling cities. Hanoi, the capital, pays homage to the nation’s iconic Communist-era leader, Ho Chi Minh, via a huge marble mausoleum. Ho Chi Minh City (formerly Saigon) has French colonial landmarks, plus Vietnamese War history museums and the Củ Chi tunnels, used by Viet Cong soldiers.","currency":"Vietnamese dong","attractions":[{"place":"Ha Long Bay","describe":"Rocky islands, junk boats & Đầu Gỗ Cave","imageUrl":"http://static.asiawebdirect.com/m/bangkok/portals/vietnam/homepage/ha-long-bay/pagePropertiesImage/ha-long-bay.jpg.jpg"},{"place":"Phú Quốc","describe":"Beach resorts, Duong Dong, Phú Quốc Park","imageUrl":"https://travel.com.vn/Images/destination/tf_160809_bien%20phu%20quoc.jpg"},{"place":"Imperial City, Hue","describe":"Royal palace within the forbidden city","imageUrl":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/La_porte_du_midi_%28Cit%C3%A9_imp%C3%A9riale%2C_Hu%C3%A9%29.jpg/1200px-La_porte_du_midi_%28Cit%C3%A9_imp%C3%A9riale%2C_Hu%C3%A9%29.jpg"},{"place":"Marble Mountains","describe":"Dramatic mountains with caves & temples","imageUrl":"https://www.vietnamonline.com/userfile/attraction/admin/2011/10/ngu%20hanh%20son%201.jpeg"}]},{"country":"Laos","description":"Laos is a Southeast Asian country traversed by the Mekong River and known for mountainous terrain, French colonial architecture, hill tribe settlements and Buddhist monasteries. Vientiane, the capital, is the site of the That Luang monument, where a reliquary reportedly houses the Buddha’s breastbone, plus the Patuxai war memorial and Talat Sao (Morning Market), a complex jammed with food, clothes and craft stalls.","currency":"Lao kip","attractions":[{"place":"Kuang Si Falls","describe":"Rushing waterfalls & natural pools","imageUrl":"http://static.asiawebdirect.com/m/bangkok/portals/laos/homepage/luang-prabang/kuang-si-waterfall/pagePropertiesImage/kuang-si-waterfall.jpg.jpg"},{"place":"Mount Phousi","describe":"Popular hiking summit with sunset views","imageUrl":"http://static.asiawebdirect.com/m/bangkok/portals/laos/homepage/luang-prabang/mount-phousi/allParagraphs/BucketComponent/ListingContainer/05/image/mount-phousi.jpg"},{"place":"Pha That Luang","describe":"Historic gold stupa over 44 m. high","imageUrl":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b6/Pha_That_Luang%2C_Vientiane%2C_Laos.jpg"},{"place":"Wat Xieng Thong","describe":"Buddhist temple with gardens & shrines","imageUrl":"https://laoshostels.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Templo-Wat-Xieng-Thong.jpg"}]},{"country":"Timor Leste","description":"Timor-Leste, or East Timor, a Southeast Asian nation occupying half the island of Timor, is ringed by coral reefs teeming with marine life. Landmarks in the capital, Dili, speak to the country's struggles for independence from Portugal in 1975 and then Indonesia in 2002. The iconic 27m-tall Cristo Rei de Dili statue sits on a hilltop high over the city, with sweeping views of the surrounding bay.","currency":"United States Dollar, Indonesian rupiah, East Timor centavo coins","attractions":[{"place":"","describe":"","imageUrl":""},{"place":"","describe":"","imageUrl":""},{"place":"","describe":"","imageUrl":""},{"place":"","describe":"","imageUrl":""}]},{"country":"Brunei","description":"Brunei is a tiny nation on the island of Borneo, in 2 distinct sections surrounded by Malaysia and the South China Sea. It's known for its beaches and biodiverse rainforest, much of it protected within reserves. The capital, Bandar Seri Begawan, is home to the opulent Jame’Asr Hassanil Bolkiah mosque and its 29 golden domes. The capital's massive Istana Nurul Iman palace is the residence of Brunei’s ruling sultan.","currency":"Brunei dollar","attractions":[{"place":"Sultan Omar Ali Saifuddin Mosque","describe":"Ornate gold-domed mosque in a lagoon","imageUrl":"https://assets.atlasobscura.com/media/W1siZiIsInVwbG9hZHMvcGxhY2VfaW1hZ2VzLzU5YWI5ODgyYjQwNWVmNjQ0ZDIyNzBiOGI0ZmZiODFjY2U2ZDlkN2YuanBnIl0sWyJwIiwidGh1bWIiLCJ4MzkwPiJdLFsicCIsImNvbnZlcnQiLCItcXVhbGl0eSA4MSAtYXV0by1vcmllbnQiXV0/59ab9882b405ef644d2270b8b4ffb81cce6d9d7f.jpg"},{"place":"Istana Nurul Iman","describe":"Sprawling royal palace with a mosque","imageUrl":"https://e-realestates.gr/wp-content/uploads/1-38.jpg"},{"place":"Jerudong Park","describe":"Amusement park rides, gardens & events","imageUrl":"https://images.snapfeed.com/images/13449.jpg"},{"place":"Royal Regalia Museum","describe":"Domed musuem with exhibits on royal life","imageUrl":"https://media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-s/07/c9/6d/05/royal-regalia-museum.jpg"}]},{"country":"Philippines","description":"The Philippines is a Southeast Asian country in the Western Pacific, comprising more than 7,000 islands. Its capital, Manila, is famous for its waterfront promenade and centuries-old Chinatown, Binondo. Intramuros, a walled city in colonial times, is the heart of Old Manila. It’s home to the baroque 17th-century San Agustin Church as well as Fort Santiago, a storied citadel and military prison.","currency":"Philippine peso","attractions":[{"place":"Boracay","describe":"White Beach & Mount Luho views","imageUrl":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/8Orpy_d2HPM/maxresdefault.jpg"},{"place":"Puerto Princesa Subterranean River National Park","describe":"Underground river, caves & national park","imageUrl":"https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-aC7WFk0V4eE/V10cKnNflQI/AAAAAAAASgM/pwtOh8g77pUiZ_Ht9L8lqHK5hX-7CpmVQCLcB/s640/1%2BPPUR.JPG"},{"place":"Mactan","describe":"Beach, seaside resort, scuba diving, casino, and snorkeling","imageUrl":"https://www.cebutours.ph/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/mactan-islands.jpg"},{"place":"Rizal Park","describe":"Large park for strolling & public events","imageUrl":"https://www.askideas.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Back-View-Of-Rizal-Monument-In-Rizal-Park.jpg"}]}]


